<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 06 at 4:25PM EDT until July 06 at 4:45PM EDT by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 445 PM EDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN ALAMANCE...NORTHEASTERN RANDOLPH...SOUTHEASTERN
GUILFORD AND NORTHWESTERN CHATHAM COUNTIES...
At 425 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Elon, or 7
miles southwest of Burlington, and is nearly stationary.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Burlington, Liberty, Alamance, Staley, Lake Mackintosh Marina, Lake
Guilford Mackintosh Marina and Snow Camp.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
